* Contributing

Efetch (or emacs-fetch) is a free and hackable software.

** Code contribution

*** Coding style

The project use [[https://github.com/bbatsov/emacs-lisp-style-guide][Emacs-lisp style guide line]] and use as possible
functional programming paradigm. So =while= and =for= loops are
banned, please use recursive function and =map= function.

*** Editing code

We recommend to use Emacs with Paredit to edit source code. You can
add the following configuration code in your =~/.emacs= to start
Paredit for all emacs-lisp files.

#+BEGIN_SRC emacs-lisp
(add-hook 'emacs-lisp-mode-hook 'paredit-mode)
#+END_SRC

Don't forget to made =M-q= to check your code indentation.

*** Commit message

Commit message format is very close than the ChangeLog format. Please
see previous commit message.

* Communications

This project follows the [[https://www.gnu.org/philosophy/kind-communication.html?ref=hvper.com][GNU Kind Communications Guidelines]].
